<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - REAR OIL SEAL AND WEAR SLEEVE - WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>WEAR SLEEVE REMOVAL</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Flywheel Housing Removed</title>
            <para>Remove the wear sleeve as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the flywheel, flywheel housing and rear oil seal carrier removed, use a hammer and
                    tap the O.D. of the wear sleeve.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>This causes the wear sleeve to expand and slide off easily.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Discard wear sleeve.</para>
                <figure id="ef1600710" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5175" filename="../figeg5/EG5175.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.10 Installing Wear Sleeve Removal Tool Collets</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600711" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5176" filename="../figeg5/EG5176.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.11 Installing Wear Sleeve Removal Sleeve Around Collets</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600712" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5177" filename="../figeg5/EG5177.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.12 Removing Wear Sleeve</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
